---
import DefaultLayout from '../../layouts/DefaultLayout.astro'
import FullWidth from '../../components/FullWidth.astro'
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/QueryIsolationComparisonTable.astro'
import FeaturePillar from '../../components/FeaturePillar.astro'
import { Link } from 'accessible-astro-components'

const technicalPillars = [
  {
    index: "01",
    title: "The Icebreaker Broker",
    description: "A hyperscaler-grade admission controller that replaces static queuing with workload-aware orchestration.",
    items: [
      "<strong>Sovereign Allocation:</strong> Instead of assigning a query to a pre-existing cluster, the Broker provisions a dedicated execution pod sized to the query's specific memory and CPU requirements.",
      "<strong>Pre-emptive Scheduling:</strong> Critical workloads can physically pre-empt lower-priority tasks, reclaiming resources at the kernel level rather than waiting for a logical slot to open."
    ]
  },
  {
    index: "02",
    title: "Ephemeral Pod Execution",
    description: "Moving the security boundary from the software layer to the hardware-enforced container boundary.",
    items: [
      "<strong>Zero-Trust Memory:</strong> By utilizing standalone K8S pods, Icebreaker ensures that every query has its own private memory heap, eliminating the 'Leaky JVM' risks found in shared Spark or Snowflake clusters.",
      "<strong>Stateless Lifecycle:</strong> Pods are born for a single query and destroyed immediately upon completion, ensuring zero data persistence or residual state."
    ]
  },
  {
    index: "03",
    title: "DataFusion Runtime",
    description: "A high-performance execution engine designed for the era of micro-isolation.",
    items: [
      "<strong>Eliminating JVM Overhead:</strong> By using a Rust-based engine, Icebreaker avoids the massive 'Cold Start' and memory management penalties that make traditional pod isolation too slow for production.",
      "<strong>VPC-Native Privacy:</strong> Execution happens within your security perimeter, governed by task-level IAM roles and security groups."
    ]
  }
];
---

<DefaultLayout title="Query Isolation | Icebreaker Data">
    <section>
        <div class="container">
            <h1 class="text-6xl font-extrabold mb-6">Query Isolation</h1>
            <p class="text-2xl leading-relaxed max-w-4xl opacity-90">
                Guarantee the secure and successful execution of every query.
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <FullWidth>
        <div class="container grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
            <div class="p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-xl border-t-4 border-(--primary-400)">
                <h4 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6 ">What's Wrong with Right-Sizing</h4>
                <ul class="list-warning text-lg space-y-4">
                    <li>Warehouses and clusters are sized for aggregate workloads.</li> 
                    <li>Individual queries have wildly different memory and compute requirements.</li>
                    <li>Auto-scaling forces overpaying for compute that may not even be optimal for the job.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
                <p class="text-xl opacity-80">
                    It is impossible to match a conventional cluster or warehouse to actual demand. You over-pay for idle compute that may not even meet your performance goals.
                </p>
                <br/>
                <p class="text-xl opacity-80">
                    Icebreaker breaks through with <strong>isolated query execution</strong>. 
                    We implement the same fine-grained isolation patterns used by hyperscalers, 
                    ensuring every query is physically sandboxed within its own ephemeral execution environment.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </FullWidth>

    <section class="bg-(--primary-400) py-24">
        <div class="container">
            <article class="mx-auto max-w-4xl rounded-3xl bg-white p-10 md:p-16 shadow-2xl text-(--neutral-800) relative overflow-hidden">
                <header class="mb-12">
                    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 text-xs font-black uppercase tracking-widest text-(--primary-500) mb-4">
                        <span class="border-2 border-(--primary-500) px-2 py-1 rounded">Key Concept</span>
                        <span>•</span>
                        <span>Technical Deep Dive</span>
                    </div>
                    <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold text-(--primary-500) leading-tight">
                        Beyond the Cluster: The Evolution of Isolation
                    </h2>
                </header>

                <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-(--neutral-700) space-y-6">
                    <p>
                        Data engineering has historically struggled with a trade-off: <strong>Performance vs. Safety.</strong> To get speed, we share resources in a "Warehouse." To get safety, we isolate workloads into dedicated "VMs." Neither model works for the high-concurrency, security-first world of Agentic AI.
                    </p>

                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-(--primary-500) pt-4">The Boundary Spectrum</h3>
                    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 my-8">
                        <div class="p-4 bg-(--neutral-100) rounded-xl border border-(--neutral-200)">
                            <h4 class="font-bold text-sm mb-2 uppercase">The VM Boundary</h4>
                            <p class="text-xs">Physical isolation, but massive overhead. High 'Cold Start' times and wasted idle resources make it impractical for individual queries.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="p-4 bg-(--neutral-100) rounded-xl border border-(--neutral-200)">
                            <h4 class="font-bold text-sm mb-2 uppercase">The Cluster Boundary</h4>
                            <p class="text-xs">Logical isolation in a shared JVM. Fast, but 'leaky.' One query can starve another or potentially access shared memory states.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="p-4 bg-(--primary-500) text-white rounded-xl shadow-lg">
                            <h4 class="font-bold text-sm mb-2 uppercase">Compute Sovereignty</h4>
                            <p class="text-xs">Physical isolation at the query level. Ephemeral pods and DataFusion provide VM-level safety with cluster-level performance.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <p>
                        The core technical problem—most famously explored in the <em>Membrane</em> research—is that imperative code and complex queries cannot be trusted in a shared-process environment. In a traditional Spark or Warehouse executor, a single unoptimized query doesn't just run slow; it threatens the integrity of the entire engine.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        Icebreaker solves this by enforcing <strong>Atomic Isolation</strong>. We move the security boundary from the software layer to the hardware-enforced container boundary. Every query—from a "greedy" agentic prompt to a multi-terabyte join—executes in its own private, sovereign world.
                    </p>

                    <div class="rounded-lg bg-(--primary-500) p-6 text-white my-8">
                        <p class="m-0 italic">
                           "By decoupling the execution lifecycle from the underlying infrastructure, Icebreaker ensures that sensitive data and demanding workloads never share a 'Membrane.' This is the same pattern hyperscalers use to protect their own multi-tenant services, now available for your private data cloud."
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <p>
                        While this ensures total integrity, it also provides the foundation for <Link href="/product/demand-shaping">Demand Shaping</Link>. Once every query is isolated, you can finally orchestrate your data stack based on the actual value of the workload, not the limitations of your cluster size.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-24">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="mb-16 text-center">
                <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">How Icebreaker Enforces Sovereignty</h2>
                <p class="text-xl mx-auto opacity-80">
                    The architecture that brings hyperscaler-grade isolation to the enterprise.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="grid gap-8 md:grid-cols-3 lg:gap-12">
                {technicalPillars.map((pillar) => (
                    <FeaturePillar 
                        index={pillar.index}
                        title={pillar.title}
                        description={pillar.description}
                        listItems={pillar.items}
                    />
                ))}
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <FullWidth>
        <div class="container py-12">
            <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Comparing Isolation Models</h2>
            <ComparisonTable title="Architectural Comparison: Icebreaker vs. Traditional Warehouses" />
        </div>
    </FullWidth>
</DefaultLayout>